oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Blues In My Mind - Rambling Rogue - 1945-12-04
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: First recording is a performance of Blues In My Mind, as performed by the Rambling Rogue (Fred Rose) (performer), second recording is a performance of Wreck Of The Old 97, as performed by an unidentified male vocalist, and third recording is a performance of It Ain't Me Babe, as performed by Johnny Cash (performer) and June Carter Cash (performer). Fourth recording is a performance of Hillbilly Music Goin' Round, as performed by Stringbean (performer).
